<h4>
    Saying the Names Right!
</h4>

<ul>
    <li>
        Whenever we use the sine function, we write the abbreviation \( \sin \),
        but when reading this out loud you always say "sine!"
    </li>
    <li>
        Whenever we use the cosine function, we write the abbreviation \( \cos \),
        but when reading this out loud you always say "cosine!"
    </li>
    <li>
        Whenever we use the tangent function, we write the abbreviation \( \tan \),
        but when reading this out loud you always say "tangent!"
    </li>
</ul>

